---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Accessibility | TechTalk Academy" 
  description="TechTalk Academy's commitment to digital accessibility and inclusive learning experiences for all."
>
  <section class="pt-32 pb-12 relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 vr-grid opacity-20"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Accessibility Statement</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400">Our commitment to inclusive digital experiences</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="glass-card p-8 md:p-12 space-y-8">
          
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Our Commitment</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              TechTalk Academy is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for all users, including people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards to our website and learning platforms.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              We believe that technology education should be accessible to everyone, regardless of ability. This commitment extends from our website to our learning experiences, where we provide multiple pathways for learners to engage with content.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Conformance Status</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) defines requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities. We strive to meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards across our digital properties.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              We recognize that accessibility is an ongoing effort, and we are committed to regular reviews and improvements of our digital content.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Accessibility Features</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We have implemented the following features to improve accessibility on our website:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-300">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Keyboard Navigation:</strong> All interactive elements are accessible via keyboard</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Screen Reader Support:</strong> Content is structured with proper headings, landmarks, and alternative text</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Color Contrast:</strong> Text and interactive elements meet WCAG contrast requirements</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Responsive Design:</strong> Content adapts to various screen sizes and zoom levels</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Clear Navigation:</strong> Consistent and predictable navigation throughout the site</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Form Accessibility:</strong> Form fields include proper labels and error handling</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Learning Experience Accessibility</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Our commitment to accessibility extends to our learning experiences:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-300 mt-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-purple-400 mt-1">●</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">VR-Enhanced, Not VR-Required:</strong> While we offer immersive VR experiences, all core learning content is available through traditional, accessible interfaces</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-purple-400 mt-1">●</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Multiple Learning Pathways:</strong> Learners can engage with content in ways that work best for their needs</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-purple-400 mt-1">●</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Accommodations:</strong> We work with learners who need specific accommodations to ensure they can fully participate in our programs</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-purple-400 mt-1">●</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Assistive Technology Support:</strong> Our learning platforms are designed to work with common assistive technologies</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Browser and Assistive Technology Compatibility</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Our website is designed to be compatible with the following:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300 mt-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-slate-500 mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Modern web browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-slate-500 mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-slate-500 mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Voice recognition software</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-slate-500 mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Screen magnification tools</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Known Limitations</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              While we strive for full accessibility, we acknowledge that some areas may have limitations:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300 mt-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1">!</span>
                <span>Some third-party content or embedded tools may not meet all accessibility standards</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1">!</span>
                <span>Certain interactive simulations may require specific capabilities</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1">!</span>
                <span>Older content may not yet be fully remediated</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              We are actively working to address these limitations and welcome feedback to help prioritize improvements.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Requesting Accommodations</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              If you need specific accommodations to participate in our programs, please contact us as early as possible. We are committed to working with learners to identify and implement appropriate accommodations.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Feedback and Contact</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website and learning experiences. If you encounter any barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-white font-semibold">TechTalk Academy Accessibility Team</p>
              <p class="text-slate-300">Email: accessibility@techtalkacademy.com</p>
              <p class="text-slate-300">Phone: (555) 123-4567</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days and to provide a resolution or plan within 30 days.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-4">Continuous Improvement</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Accessibility is not a one-time effort but an ongoing commitment. We regularly:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300 mt-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">→</span>
                <span>Conduct accessibility audits of our digital properties</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">→</span>
                <span>Train our team on accessibility best practices</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">→</span>
                <span>Incorporate accessibility into our design and development processes</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-1">→</span>
                <span>Review and respond to user feedback</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Back Link -->
        <div class="mt-8 text-center">
          <a href="/" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"/>
            </svg>
            Back to Home
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
